		{
			dependencies: ["7A3F9B2E5D8C1A4F"]
			description: ["Wrought Iron is produced by smelting Iron in a Campfire — the slow, low-heat process retains a fibrous structure that vanilla smelting destroys. GT hand tools and machine hulls require it in plate form. Firebricks are the structural lining of every early GT smelting multiblock: mix Clay Dust and Sand into Fireclay, compress it into Compressed Fireclay, then fire it. Neither step is optional — Wrought Iron gates hulls, Firebricks gate the Primitive Blast Furnace."]
			id: "2B8D4F6A9E1C3B7D"
