			}]
			title: "LV Electric Pump"
			x: 42.0d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"7752E1BB3D5CFC2D"
				"235DE680E4EED95B"
			]
			description: ["The LV Assembler is the inflection point of GregTech automation. It accepts up to nine input items and produces any valid crafting recipe output automatically — no shaped table, no player. Feed it via Conveyor Module from sorted chests and it outputs directly to a downstream belt. The Assembler halves the manual crafting burden of every machine you build from this point forward. Set up dedicated recipes for the components you produce most: circuits, cables, plates, pipes."]
			id: "34CDA1840B3ED98D"
			rewards: [{
				count: 5
				id: "12340000AABB0006"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			shape: "gear"
			size: 1.5d
			tasks: [{
				id: "038A52C2883B77EF"
				item: "gtceu:lv_assembler"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "The Assembler"
			x: 46.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["34CDA1840B3ED98D"]
			description: ["The LV Wiremill produces wire from ingots at 2x or better yield compared to manual hammer-shaping. Copper and Tin wire demand scales directly with your machine count — every motor, every circuit, every cable run requires them at volume. The Wiremill is also the only way to produce Fine Wire and Very Fine Wire at MV tier, making it a non-negotiable machine before the Electric Blast Furnace. Automate a continuous Copper and Tin wire output loop before you need coil wire."]
			id: "023807B9C94AFD56"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "12340000AABB0007"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "3FD47F14297E6CA0"
				item: "gtceu:lv_wiremill"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "LV Wiremill"
			x: 48.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["34CDA1840B3ED98D"]
			description: ["The LV Bender produces Plates, Curved Plates, and Rings from ingots and rods — at double the plate yield of manual hammer-shaping. Curved Plates are required for fluid pipes and machine casings; Rings appear in motors, pumps, and pistons. The Bender is the only way to produce Ring shapes, and its plate efficiency makes it mandatory for any factory operating at scale. Dedicate one Bender to Steel output for constant casing demand."]
			id: "2C70B19C5BB3715D"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "12340000AABB0008"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "1EC24699C9007DF0"
				item: "gtceu:lv_bender"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "LV Bender"
			x: 48.0d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["34CDA1840B3ED98D"]
			description: ["The LV Lathe produces Rods, Bolts, Screws, and Lens shapes from ingots and plates. Bolts and Screws are required for circuit assembly, machine component crafting, and several multiblock structures. The Lathe is the only GT machine that produces Lens shapes — needed later for optical sensors and the Distillation Tower. Set it producing Steel Rods and Iron Bolts on an automated loop from day one."]
			id: "2A92915EF19FCDBA"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "12340000AABB0009"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "73EE8A5F5ED16354"
				item: "gtceu:lv_lathe"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "LV Lathe"
			x: 48.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5FC62C3CE74A6BE5"]
			description: ["The GT electric ore processing chain extends yield far beyond Create's Crushing Wheels. The full chain: Macerator (crushed ore, 2x base) → Ore Washer with distilled water (purified crushed ore + stone dust byproduct) → Thermal Centrifuge (ore dust + a rare secondary byproduct unique to each ore) → Chemical Bath for select ores (third byproduct). Assembling the full chain yields 3 to 4 distinct output items per raw ore input. Build the lane now so it comes online with the rest of the machine floor."]
			id: "1ECC2289134EAEE4"
			rewards: [{
				count: 2
				id: "12340000AABB000A"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "562A45E6CECFB4EA"
				title: "Plan the Electric Ore Chain"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Electric Ore Chain"
			x: 42.0d
			y: 3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1ECC2289134EAEE4"]
			description: ["The LV Ore Washer processes Crushed Ore with Distilled Water into Purified Crushed Ore plus a Stone Dust byproduct. Purified ore macerated downstream has a higher chance at secondary byproduct dusts compared to direct-macerating raw ore. The key input is Distilled Water — regular water will not work. Produce it from a Steam Boiler condensate loop or, later, in the Distillery. An LV Pump connected to a fluid tank provides sufficient throughput at early volumes."]
			id: "1D9839C02092B73B"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "12340000AABB000B"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "7CD8F3EAE7BABD88"
				item: "gtceu:lv_ore_washer"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "LV Ore Washer"
			x: 44.0d
			y: 3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["1D9839C02092B73B"]
			description: ["The LV Thermal Centrifuge processes Purified Crushed Ore into Ore Dust plus a secondary byproduct dust unique to each ore type. Iron gives a chance at Tin Dust. Gold gives a chance at Copper Dust. Copper gives a chance at Gold Dust at low probability. Rare ores like Platinum have extremely valuable centrifuge byproducts obtainable through no other method. Run the Thermal Centrifuge on every ore variety you process — the byproduct accumulation compounds into a real secondary income stream over time."]
			id: "3B07FADAB8B6CE4F"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "12340000AABB000C"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "3F8AB991F45C15CE"
				item: "gtceu:lv_thermal_centrifuge"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "LV Thermal Centrifuge"
			x: 46.0d
			y: 3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3B07FADAB8B6CE4F"]
			description: ["The LV Chemical Bath adds a reagent soak step to ore processing, yielding a third byproduct output for specific ores. It also automates PCB etching: the Resin Circuit Board in the greg chapter was etched manually; the Chemical Bath runs this continuously with Sodium Persulfate or Iron(III) Chloride solution. Build it alongside the Chemical Reactor — the Chemical Bath consumes reagents the Reactor produces, forming a self-sustaining loop."]
			id: "20078A3EE4C9425E"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "12340000AABB000D"
				item: "lightmanscurrency:coin_gold"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "77F707AE8886CE03"
