				item: "gtceu:mv_electrolyzer"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "MV Electrolyzer"
			x: 70.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5A5B000BCCDD000B"]
			description: ["The MV Chemical Reactor handles fluid-reagent chemistry at medium voltage — Sulfuric Acid from Sulfur and Water, Hydrochloric Acid, Sodium Persulfate for PCB etching, and the Chromite leaching chain. Unlike the LV reactor it accepts simultaneous fluid and solid inputs with wider throughput limits. Set it producing Sulfuric Acid continuously from the start — it is consumed by Aluminium processing, Platinum group chemistry, and nearly every industrial leaching reaction that follows in HV and beyond."]
			id: "5A5B000DCCDD000D"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
